Digit Puzzle
Description

This program builds the longest possible sequence by connecting numbers using:

the last two digits of one number

the first two digits of another number

Each number can be used only once.

Requirements

Java 21 or higher

How to Run

Open a terminal in the folder containing the .jar file.

Run:

java -jar puzzleProject-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar source.txt

Input Format:
Plain .txt file
One number per line
Digits only
Minimum length: 4 characters

Example:
608017
248460
962282
994725
177092

Output
The program prints:
The longest constructed sequence

Its length

Example:

The biggest puzzle is: 24846080177092
The length is: 14

Notes

The program works with any valid input file.

No additional tools or IDE are required.

Fully executable from the command line.